## What Is Artificial Intelligence?

Imagine a **calculator** and a **music streaming app**.

A calculator gives answers only when you tell it exactly what to do.  
A music app learns what you like and suggests new songs.

**Artificial Intelligence (AI)** is when machines learn from data and make decisions, instead of following only fixed rules written by humans.

---

## Traditional Software vs AI Systems

### Traditional Software (Rule-Based)
Traditional software works by following clear instructions.

Input â†’ Fixed rules written by humans â†’ Output

Example:
If temperature > 30 â†’ Turn on fan
If temperature â‰¤ 30 â†’ Keep fan off

Problems with traditional software:
- Every rule must be written manually
- Difficult to handle new or unexpected situations
- Updating rules takes time

---

### AI Systems (Learning-Based)
AI systems learn patterns from data.

Input data â†’ Learning algorithm â†’ Model â†’ Output

Instead of writing rules, we give examples.  
The system figures out patterns on its own.

